\

\f0\b Docket:
\f1\b0  KASBAH-2026-001\
\

\f0\b CLAIMS
\f1\b0 \
\

\f0\b Claim 1.
\f1\b0  A computer-implemented method for biomimetic threat detection comprising: \
(a) implementing Aboriginal fire pattern confidence decay algorithm that tracks pattern usage frequency, applies exponential decay based on time since last effective use, triggers controlled burn when confidence falls below threshold, and regenerates pattern from symbolic regression; \
(b) implementing bee colony biodiversity correlation scoring that maintains multiple detection tiers, calculates co-occurrence scores between tiers, applies biodiversity bonus when multiple tiers detect same threat, and penalizes monoculture detection; \
(c) implementing fungal mycelial network threat propagation that models threat nodes as mycelial network nodes, calculates nutrient flow between nodes, implements symbiotic relationships, and implements competitive relationships; \
(d) combining outputs through weighted geometric mean integrity check to produce final threat assessment.\
\

\f0\b Claim 2.
\f1\b0  The method of Claim 1, wherein Aboriginal fire pattern confidence decay uses formula: confidence(t) = confidence(0) \'d7 e^(-\uc0\u955  \'d7 t / 3600), where \u955  is decay rate between 0.01 and 0.1 per hour.\
\

\f0\b Claim 3.
\f1\b0  The method of Claim 1, wherein bee colony biodiversity maintains exactly three detection tiers: Tier 1 for basic patterns, Tier 2 for advanced patterns, Tier 3 for frontier patterns.\
\

\f0\b Claim 4.
\f1\b0  The method of Claim 1, wherein biodiversity bonus is 1.5 when all three tiers detect same threat, 1.2 when two tiers detect, 1.0 when only one tier detects.\
\

\f0\b Claim 5.
\f1\b0  The method of Claim 1, further comprising: implementing PPP (Pre-Transmission Protection) nature-inspired modules selected from the group consisting of: Aboriginal fire decay, beeodiversity correlation, fungi mycelial propagation, LanzaTech transform, soil security, breathe easy filtration.\
\

\f0\b Claim 6.
\f1\b0  The method of Claim 1, wherein fungal mycelial network calculates connection strength based on co-occurrence frequency, temporal proximity, and semantic similarity between threat nodes.\
\

\f0\b Claim 7.
\f1\b0  A non-transitory computer-readable medium storing instructions that, when executed by one or more processors, cause the one or more processors to perform the method of Claim 1.\
\

\f0\b Claim 8.
\f1\b0  A system comprising: one or more processors; and memory storing instructions that, when executed by the one or more processors, cause the system to perform the method of Claim 1.\
